data.name: textBox1.Text
data.value:
Procedure:
Starting Position:
- Stand upright with feet shoulder-width apart, arms at your sides.
Squat Down:
- Bend your knees and lower into a squat, placing your hands flat on the ground in front of you.
Kick Back:
- Jump your feet backward into a plank position, ensuring your body forms a straight line from head to heels.
Push-Up (Optional):
- Lower your chest to the ground and perform a push-up for added difficulty.
Jump Forward:
- Jump your feet back toward your hands to return to the squat position.
Explosive Jump:
- From the squat, jump upward explosively, reaching your arms overhead.
Land Softly:
- Land gently with slightly bent knees to reduce impact and prepare for the next repetition.
Repeat:
- Continue performing the movements in a smooth, fluid sequence.
Time, Sets, and Reps:
- Time (HIIT): Perform for 40 seconds per interval. - Sets: Include 3 sets during the workout. - Reps: Aim for 8–12 reps per set or AMAP (as many as possible) if timed.

data.name: workoutPlan1_Content.Text
data.value:
Procedure:
Starting Position:
- Stand upright with your feet together and arms relaxed at your sides.
Jump and Spread:
- Jump up, spreading your legs shoulder-width apart while raising your arms overhead in a wide arc.
Return to Start:
- Jump again, bringing your feet back together and lowering your arms to your sides.
Repeat:
- Continue moving in a fluid and rhythmic motion.
Time, Sets, and Reps:
- Time (HIIT): Perform for 40 seconds per interval. - Sets: Include 3 sets in your workout. - Reps: Aim for 30–50 reps per set (or AMAP if working for time).
